.TH "TEMPORAL.DURATION.DURATION" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.Duration.Duration \- Temporal.Duration()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Temporal.Duration()\f[B]\f[R] constructor creates
\f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] objects.
.PP
This constructor allows you to create instances by directly supplying
the underlying data.
Like all other \f[CR]Temporal\f[R] classes, you should usually construct
\f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] objects using the
\f[CR]Temporal.Duration.from()\f[R] static method, which can handle a
variety of input types.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
new Temporal.Duration()
new Temporal.Duration(years)
new Temporal.Duration(years, months)
new Temporal.Duration(years, months, weeks)
new Temporal.Duration(years, months, weeks, days)
new Temporal.Duration(years, months, weeks, days, hours)
new Temporal.Duration(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes)
new Temporal.Duration(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds)
new Temporal.Duration(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds)
new Temporal.Duration(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds)
new Temporal.Duration(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds)
.EE
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] \f[CR]Temporal.Duration()\f[R] can only be constructed
with \f[CR]new\f[R].
Attempting to call it without \f[CR]new\f[R] throws a
\f[CR]TypeError\f[R].
.RE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]years\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Number of years, or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] (which is treated as
\f[CR]0\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]months\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Number of months, or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] (which is treated as
\f[CR]0\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]weeks\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Number of weeks, or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] (which is treated as
\f[CR]0\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]days\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Number of days, or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] (which is treated as
\f[CR]0\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]hours\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Number of hours, or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] (which is treated as
\f[CR]0\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]minutes\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Number of minutes, or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] (which is treated as
\f[CR]0\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]seconds\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Number of seconds, or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] (which is treated as
\f[CR]0\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]milliseconds\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Number of milliseconds, or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] (which is treated as
\f[CR]0\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]microseconds\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Number of microseconds, or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] (which is treated as
\f[CR]0\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]nanoseconds\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Number of nanoseconds, or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] (which is treated as
\f[CR]0\f[R]).
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] object, possibly unbalanced, with the
specified components.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]RangeError\f[R]
Thrown in one of the following cases:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Any of the parameters is not an integer (including non\-finite values).
.IP \(bu 2
A calendar unit (years, months, weeks) has an absolute value ≥ 2\(ha32.
.IP \(bu 2
The non\-calendar part of the duration (days and below), when expressed
in seconds, has an absolute value ≥ 2\(ha53.
.RE
